Robert Amen - Wikipedia





















 






Robert Amen

From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia


					Jump to:					navigation, 					search

Robert M. Amen served as the Chairman and CEO of International Flavors and Fragrances from 2006 to 2009.[1]
Early life and career[edit]
Amen born in New York City, NY and holds a bachelor's degree from Boston College and a master in business administration from Columbia Business School in 1973.
Amen joined International Paper in 1980 as an Assistant Treasurer. From 1996 to 2000, he served as President of International Paper, Europe. He was an Executive Vice President from 2000 to 2003 and President from 2003 to 2006.[2][3]
